From Lloyd Carr Subject Re Yamaha vs Honda opinions In a previous article Ju says KEITH NUETZMAN writes A friend of mine who's probably reading this right now just bought a new Yamaha Virago After spending hours very late one chilly evening watching him struggle with the bolts had to remove the right peg loosen the brake pedal I've pretty much decided never to get this particular model unless he or someone else wants to change the oil filter for Compared to the minute change he was used to for his Honda this is just a design flaw oversight in my Patricia Sure don't know what bike was being worked on but it sure wasn't a I've owned both the and and you can do the filter change in about mins and nothing has to be Obviously the new bike was modified as the stock machine is simple to work Watching for imitators Lloyd Carr DoD